Photo: suppliedAndreas Mathios has a little fun. Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories THE Kloof &amp; Highway SPCA socialisation kennels were a hive of activity this past weekend with our annual dog box fund-raising event. A total of 34 people were locked in 24 kennels for 24-hours from 12pm on Friday, 26 May until 12pm on Saturday, 27 May to raise funds for the Kloof and Highway SPCA. The funds raised will be used in the Kloof and Highway SPCA's fight against the prevention of cruelty to all animals. Donations are still coming through at this stage.The SPCA thanked to each of the 2017 SPCA Dog Box participants for being part of this fund-raiser. "Your time, commitment and support of this event is greatly appreciated and thank you for braving the cold to make a difference in the lives of animals in our community. A special thank you to every person and company who made a financial contribution towards the bail money of the dog box participants, and who contributed towards the fund-raising event and helped ensure it was a great success," said Lisa M rck marketing manager. - Supplied.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.